    "href": "index.html",
    "title": "Data Aanlysis",
    "section": "",
    "text": "This course is a required offering in the English Taught Program in International Business (ETP) at Shih Chien University, taught by Yu-You Liou. It is designed to equip students with practical skills in data analysis and communication through the modern R ecosystem.\nThe primary objective of the course is to develop students’ ability to explore, analyze, and present data effectively. A central focus is placed on data visualization using ggplot2, with an emphasis on understanding the grammar of graphics as a principled framework for building clear and informative figures. Students will learn to translate analytical findings into compelling visual narratives suitable for academic and professional audiences.\nThe required textbook is ggplot2: Elegant Graphics for Data Analysis by Hadley Wickham, freely available at ggplot2-book.org."
  },
