  {
    "objectID": "r.html#authoring-documents-with-r-markdown-and-generating-pdf-output",
    "href": "r.html#authoring-documents-with-r-markdown-and-generating-pdf-output",
    "title": "Data Aanlysis",
    "section": "Authoring Documents with R Markdown and Generating PDF Output",
    "text": "Authoring Documents with R Markdown and Generating PDF Output\nR Markdown is a document format that integrates prose, code, and computational output within a single reproducible file. The following steps outline the process of creating an R Markdown document and rendering it as a PDF.\n\nStep 1: Install Required Packages\nExecute the following commands in the RStudio Console:\ninstall.packages(\"rmarkdown\")\ninstall.packages(\"knitr\")\n\n\nStep 2: Install a LaTeX Distribution\nPDF rendering requires a LaTeX engine. The tinytex package provides a lightweight, self-contained LaTeX distribution suitable for most use cases:\ninstall.packages(\"tinytex\")\ntinytex::install_tinytex()\nRestart RStudio after installation to ensure the LaTeX binaries are correctly registered.\n\n\nStep 3: Create a New R Markdown File\n\nFrom the RStudio menu, select: File → New File → R Markdown…\nSpecify a title and author in the dialogue box; set the default output format to PDF\nClick OK to generate the template file\n\n\n\nStep 4: Configure the YAML Header\nEvery R Markdown document begins with a YAML front matter block delimited by ---. This block controls document metadata and output settings:\n---\ntitle: \"Assignment Title\"\nauthor: \"Full Name (Student ID)\"\ndate: \"2024-01-01\"\noutput: pdf_document\n---\n\n\nStep 5: Write Document Content\nR Markdown uses standard Markdown syntax for formatting prose, supplemented by fenced code chunks for embedding R code:\n\n\n\nSyntax\nRendered Output\n\n\n\n\n# Heading 1\nFirst-level heading\n\n\n## Heading 2\nSecond-level heading\n\n\n**bold**\nbold\n\n\n*italic*\nitalic\n\n\nFenced code block with {r}\nExecuted R code with output\n\n\n\nExample code chunk:\n\nsummary(mtcars)\n\n\n\n      mpg             cyl             disp             hp       \n Min.   :10.40   Min.   :4.000   Min.   : 71.1   Min.   : 52.0  \n 1st Qu.:15.43   1st Qu.:4.000   1st Qu.:120.8   1st Qu.: 96.5  \n Median :19.20   Median :6.000   Median :196.3   Median :123.0  \n Mean   :20.09   Mean   :6.188   Mean   :230.7   Mean   :146.7  \n 3rd Qu.:22.80   3rd Qu.:8.000   3rd Qu.:326.0   3rd Qu.:180.0  \n Max.   :33.90   Max.   :8.000   Max.   :472.0   Max.   :335.0  \n      drat             wt             qsec             vs        \n Min.   :2.760   Min.   :1.513   Min.   :14.50   Min.   :0.0000  \n 1st Qu.:3.080   1st Qu.:2.581   1st Qu.:16.89   1st Qu.:0.0000  \n Median :3.695   Median :3.325   Median :17.71   Median :0.0000  \n Mean   :3.597   Mean   :3.217   Mean   :17.85   Mean   :0.4375  \n 3rd Qu.:3.920   3rd Qu.:3.610   3rd Qu.:18.90   3rd Qu.:1.0000  \n Max.   :4.930   Max.   :5.424   Max.   :22.90   Max.   :1.0000  \n       am              gear            carb      \n Min.   :0.0000   Min.   :3.000   Min.   :1.000  \n 1st Qu.:0.0000   1st Qu.:3.000   1st Qu.:2.000  \n Median :0.0000   Median :4.000   Median :2.000  \n Mean   :0.4062   Mean   :3.688   Mean   :2.812  \n 3rd Qu.:1.0000   3rd Qu.:4.000   3rd Qu.:4.000  \n Max.   :1.0000   Max.   :5.000   Max.   :8.000  \n\n\n\n\nStep 6: Render to PDF\nClick the Knit button in the RStudio toolbar, or use the keyboard shortcut Ctrl+Shift+K (Windows/Linux) or Cmd+Shift+K (macOS), and select Knit to PDF.\n\nNote on CJK character rendering: If Chinese, Japanese, or Korean characters appear as missing glyphs in the PDF output, specify an alternative LaTeX engine in the YAML header:\noutput:\n  pdf_document:\n    latex_engine: xelatex\nheader-includes:\n  - \\usepackage{fontspec}\n  - \\setmainfont{Noto Sans CJK TC}"
  },
  {
    "objectID": "prob.html#submission-requirements",
    "href": "prob.html#submission-requirements",
    "title": "Data Aanlysis",
    "section": "Submission Requirements",
    "text": "Submission Requirements\n\n⚠️ All assignments must be submitted using the official template provided below.\nSubmissions that are missing any of the following elements will receive a grade of zero. This policy is non-negotiable.\n\n\nTemplate\nCopy the following template as the starting point for every submission. Replace all placeholder values before submitting.\n\n---\ntitle: \"Ex. X\"\nauthor: \"Full Name (Student ID)\"\ndate: \"`r Sys.Date()`\"\noutput: pdf_document\n---\n\nknitr::opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE)\n\nprint(uuid::UUIDgenerate())\n\n## Question 1\n\n*(Write your response here.)*\n\n## Question 2\n\n*(Write your response here.)*\n\n\n\nChecklist\nBefore submitting, verify that your document satisfies all of the following criteria:\n\nThe title field in the YAML header is completed\nThe author field includes both your full name and student ID\nThe final document must be submitted strictly in .pdf format.\nThe document’s name should be ex?-id-name.pdf, eg (ex1-d10627008-Oliver.pdf)"
  },
